The older woman’s voice trembles with fury.
"I warned you! I warned you, and now look what’s happening!"
The other figure—short, energetic—throws up his hands. He replies, voice low but firm, before turning on his heel and marching up the path, vanishing around a bend.

Mrs. Aster exhales sharply, as if she’s been punched in the gut.
"Fool woman..." she mutters under her breath. She wipes at her eyes, composing herself before walking straight past you.

"Mrs. Aster?" you ask, instinctively.

She gives you a tight smile, but her eyes are clouded with something—fear? Guilt?
"It’s nothing, dear. Nothing at all."

But her hands are trembling as she walks away.
